  "text": "Let S g stand for the scalar curvature of g, and S p \u00f0o\u00de be the set consisting of the positive smooth solutions U \u00bc \u00f0u; v\u00de of (0.3) with phase o and nonlinear term u p\u00c01 . Namely, Theorem 0.1 (The 3-dimensional case-Druet and Hebey [CITATION_1] for all x A M. Then (0.3) possesses a smooth positive mountain pass solution. Moreover, for any p A \u00f02; 6\u00de, and any y A \u00f00; 1\u00de, there exists C > 0 such that for any o 0 A K 0 \u00f00\u00de, and any U A S p \u00f0o 0 \u00de, kUk C 2; y e C, where S p \u00f0o 0 \u00de is as in (0.4) and K 0 \u00f00\u00de is as in (0.5). Assuming again (0.6), there also holds that for any y A \u00f00; 1\u00de, kUk C 2; y e C for all U A S 6 \u00f0o 0 \u00de and all o 0 A K 0 \u00f0o\u00de, where C > 0 does not depend on o 0 and U.",
